# Store Location Address as Business Pickup Address

## **Executive Summary**
This feature allows merchants to easily configure their **Business Pickup Address** in the Merchant Dashboard without manually inputting the address. By enabling a toggle, the system auto-populates the pickup address using the merchant’s **Store Location Address**, saving setup time and reducing errors.
## Background
Currently, merchants must manually input their pickup address, even when it matches their store address. This leads to unnecessary redundancy, risk of mismatch, and onboarding friction. Automating this will streamline setup.
## Business Objective
*   Simplify merchant setup of shipping and pickup settings.
*   Ensure consistency between **store location** and **pickup address**.
*   Reduce merchant errors when configuring pickup addresses.
## **Scope of Solution**
*   Add a **toggle switch** in the Merchant Dashboard under **Shipping Settings > Business Pickup Address**.
    *   If enabled: Pickup address auto-populates from the store location.
    *   If disabled: Merchant enters address manually.
*   Prerequisite: Merchant must select a store before enabling toggle.
## Business Requirements

| **BR ID** | **Requirement** |
| ---| --- |
| BR-PU01 | Merchant can enable toggle to auto-populate pickup address with store location. |
| BR-PU02 | Merchant can disable toggle and manually input pickup address. |
| BR-PU03 | Auto-populated pickup address updates automatically if the store location is updated. |
| BR-PU04 | Toggle cannot be enabled without selecting a store first. |
| BR-PU05 | If merchant switches from one store to another, pickup address updates accordingly. |
| BR-PU06 | If store is deleted, pickup address becomes invalid and system prompts merchant. |
| BR-PU07 | Disabling toggle clears auto-filled address fields and enables manual entry. |
| BR-PU08 | Re-enabling toggle overwrites manual entry with store location address (confirmation required). |
| BR-PU09 | If no store exists in the account, error is displayed and merchant must add a store. |

## Stakeholder Analysis
*   **Merchants:** Configure pickup address faster and with fewer errors.
*   **Consumers:** Experience consistent and reliable pickup locations.
*   **Operations/Support:** Fewer merchant complaints about shipping errors.
